blockhost-broker (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add optional dns_zone field to allocation responses
  * Drop root: run as dedicated blockhost user with capabilities
  * Add CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE for DNS on port 53
  * Built-in authoritative DNS server for hex-based AAAA records

 -- Blockhost <contact@blockhost.io>  Thu, 12 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000

blockhost-broker (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * V2 contracts: overwrite-on-duplicate, capacity tracking, re-registration
  * Legacy contract monitoring during migration
  * Test contract support with auto-expiring 24h allocations
  * Post-approval tunnel verification (release on no WG handshake)
  * NDP proxy management for allocated prefixes
  * Re-request support (update pubkey for existing allocation)
  * Request ID prefix on encrypted responses for stale detection
  * ECIES V1 fallback decryption
  * Debian packaging with debconf setup wizard

 -- Blockhost <contact@blockhost.io>  Sun, 08 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000

blockhost-broker (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Rust implementation
  * On-chain authentication via NFT contract ownership
  * Lazy polling for request processing (no unbounded loops)
  * Silent rejections (requests expire naturally)
  * ECIES encryption compatible with Python eciespy
  * WireGuard peer management
  * SQLite-based IPAM database

 -- Blockhost <contact@blockhost.io>  Sun, 02 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000
